ages critical thinking, and sometimes challenges conventional knowledge in the field. The combination of the author's multicultural academic and journalistic background contributes to a balance of diverse perspectives and world views on cultural theories and discourses. The book is ideal for courses in Intercultural Communication with study cases, discussion topics and class activities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCognition and culture. 0aCognitive neuroscience. 0aCommunication and culture. 0aIntercultural communication. 0aSocial evolution. 4aContemporary Society. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aIntercultural communication, Cross-cultural management, Diversity management, Cultural intelligence, Cultural neuroscience.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048536511zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048536511423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048536511/original  a978-3-11-060644-7  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles